"a.脾气暴躁的；阴沉的 【英】 adj.脾气暴躁的(bad- tempered)；阴沉的(menacing or threatening) 【记】 sur(=sir先生)+ly→ 像高高在上的先生一般 【例】 a surly old man/surly weather adj. 脾气暴躁的 = gruff = domineering 【记】sur = sir, ly－像先生一般高高在上的－脾气暴躁的 【记】源自sir，先生，贵族，象贵族老爷一样傲慢 surly (adj.)  1570s, ""haughty, imperious,"" alteration of Middle English sirly ""lordly, imperious"" (14c.), literally ""like a sir,"" from sir + -ly (1). The meaning ""rude, gruff"" is first attested 1660s. For sense development, compare lordly, and German herrisch ""domineering, imperious,"" from Herr ""master, lord."" Related: Surliness."
